    "body": "```\n[src/bundle/file.rs:20:9] self.path() = \"/KMiri/tests/os/target/miri/x86_64-unknown-none/debug/os-osdk-bin\"\n\nthread 'main' (47897) panicked at src/bundle/file.rs:20:38:\ncalled `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value: Os { code: 2, kind: NotFound, message: \"No such file or directory\" }\n```\n\nThis is because osdk intentionally [doesn't pass `--target`](https://github.com/KMiri-rs/asterinas/blob/f849da3848e8264afcb8a93e8f9f9ab99ac2a04e/osdk/src/commands/build/mod.rs#L276-L279) when building the elf, while the artifact path based on arch doesn't consist.\n\n```\n$ ll /KMiri/tests/os/target/miri/x86_64-unknown-none/debug/os-osdk-bin\nls: cannot access '/KMiri/tests/os/target/miri/x86_64-unknown-none/debug/os-osdk-bin': No such file or directory\n$ ll /KMiri/tests/os/target/miri/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/debug/os-osdk-bin\n-rw-r--r-- 2 root root 9.5K Apr  8 01:43 /KMiri/tests/os/target/miri/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/debug/os-osdk-bin\n```\n\nMiri can handle [no_std](https://github.com/KMiri-rs/miri/blob/cc2d666003657a5adf4b5dc7e742888310295e97/README.md?plain=1#L528) crates based on the target name. So we still need to pass `--target` to miri.",
